{"video_id": "Sw-oGkaIUIY", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | SB 1.16.2 | 08-01-2023", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sw-oGkaIUIY", "duration": 968, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 3.64, "text": " Om Agyana Timiraandhasya Gyananjanishalakaya"}, {"start": 3.64, "end": 7.7, "text": " Chaksharunmilitam Yena Tasmai Shri Gurave Namaha"}, {"start": 7.7, "end": 11.620000000000001, "text": " Nama Om Vishnupadaya Krishna Preshthaya Bhutale"}, {"start": 11.620000000000001, "end": 15.6, "text": " Shri Mate Bhaktivedanta Swamin Nithinamine"}, {"start": 15.6, "end": 20.14, "text": " Namaste Saraswate Deve Gauravani Pracharine"}, {"start": 20.14, "end": 24.28, "text": " Nirvishesha Shunyavadi Paschatya Deshatarine"}, {"start": 24.28, "end": 28.3, "text": " Jaya Shri Krishna Chaitanya Prabhu Nithyananda"}, {"start": 28.3, "end": 32.92, "text": " Shri Advaita Gadadhara Shri Vasadi Gauravakta Vrinda"}, {"start": 32.92, "end": 37.4, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare"}, {"start": 37.4, "end": 41.7, "text": " Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"}, {"start": 41.7, "end": 44.78, "text": " Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya"}, {"start": 44.78, "end": 48.7, "text": " Narayanam Namaskritya Naram Chai Vanarottamam"}, {"start": 48.7, "end": 53.06, "text": " Deveem Saraswateem Vyasam Tato Jayam Udhirayet"}, {"start": 54.16, "end": 58.16, "text": " In this session we will be discussing from the second verse of the 16th chapter"}, {"start": 58.160000000000004, "end": 60.02, "text": " of the first canto of Shri Madbhagavatam."}, {"start": 61.480000000000004, "end": 65.72, "text": " Sa Uttarasya Tanayam Upayema Iravatim"}, {"start": 65.72, "end": 69.44, "text": " Janame Jaya Adim Chaturaha"}, {"start": 69.44, "end": 73.12, "text": " Tasyam Utpadyat Sutan"}, {"start": 73.12, "end": 76.7, "text": " The meaning of this verse is"}, {"start": 76.7, "end": 80.14, "text": " King Parikshit married the daughter of King Uttara"}, {"start": 80.14, "end": 84.46000000000001, "text": " and begot four sons headed by Maharaj"}, {"start": 84.46000000000001, "end": 86.02000000000001, "text": " Janame Jaya"}, {"start": 88.16, "end": 95.16, "text": " So this chapter describes how Parikshit received the age of Kali."}, {"start": 95.16, "end": 103.16, "text": " Parikshit ascended the throne as the emperor of the world after Yudhishthir Maharaj Nipanavajiru time."}, {"start": 103.16, "end": 109.16, "text": " Then he married and begot four sons."}, {"start": 109.16, "end": 112.16, "text": " He married the daughter of King Uttara."}, {"start": 112.16, "end": 115.47999999999999, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada explains the purport."}, {"start": 115.47999999999999, "end": 117.47999999999999, "text": " Maharaj Uttara was the son of Virudhara."}, {"start": 117.48, "end": 127.48, "text": " And this Maharaj Uttara was the maternal uncle of Maharaj Parikshit."}, {"start": 127.48, "end": 129.48000000000002, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 129.48000000000002, "end": 131.48000000000002, "text": " Or how is this relationship?"}, {"start": 131.48000000000002, "end": 137.48000000000002, "text": " Because when the Pandavas were living incognito in kingdom of Virudhara,"}, {"start": 137.48000000000002, "end": 144.48000000000002, "text": " Arjuna was instructing Virudhara's daughter."}, {"start": 144.48000000000002, "end": 146.48000000000002, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 146.48, "end": 151.48, "text": " of course Arjuna was in disguise as a dance teacher."}, {"start": 151.48, "end": 155.48, "text": " Then when later on Virudhara came to know that"}, {"start": 155.48, "end": 160.48, "text": " this Arjuna as a dance teacher was not ordinary dance teacher but he was Arjuna."}, {"start": 160.48, "end": 165.48, "text": " Then Virudhara wanted to marry his daughter to Arjuna."}, {"start": 165.48, "end": 170.48, "text": " But Arjuna refused because Arjuna said as a teacher I am like the father."}, {"start": 170.48, "end": 173.48, "text": " I am the position of a father."}, {"start": 173.48, "end": 174.48, "text": " So I can't marry her."}, {"start": 174.48, "end": 175.48, "text": " But my son can marry her."}, {"start": 175.48, "end": 183.48, "text": " So Arjuna's son Abhimanyu, he married Virudhara's daughter."}, {"start": 183.48, "end": 190.48, "text": " Now Parikshit is the son of Abhimanyu."}, {"start": 190.48, "end": 203.48, "text": " So Uttara, sorry, Iravati, the daughter of Maharaj Uttara,"}, {"start": 203.48000000000002, "end": 211.48000000000002, "text": " who is the brother-in-law of Abhimanyu,"}, {"start": 211.48000000000002, "end": 215.48000000000002, "text": " is actually a cousin to Parikshit."}, {"start": 215.48000000000002, "end": 222.48000000000002, "text": " So Iravati was a cousin sister of Maharaj Parikshit."}, {"start": 222.48000000000002, "end": 231.48000000000002, "text": " Maharaj Uttara's daughter and"}, {"start": 231.48000000000002, "end": 239.48000000000002, "text": " Abhimanyu's son Parikshit were cousins."}, {"start": 239.48000000000002, "end": 243.48000000000002, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada says cousin brothers and sisters were allowed to get married"}, {"start": 243.48000000000002, "end": 248.48000000000002, "text": " if they did not belong to the same gotra or family."}, {"start": 248.48000000000002, "end": 250.48000000000002, "text": " So this is the important point."}, {"start": 250.48000000000002, "end": 253.48000000000002, "text": " Even though they are cousin brother and sister,"}, {"start": 253.48000000000002, "end": 257.48, "text": " they can get married if they don't belong to the same gotra."}, {"start": 257.48, "end": 259.48, "text": " Gotra means family."}, {"start": 259.48, "end": 261.48, "text": " In the Vedic system of marriage,"}, {"start": 261.48, "end": 265.48, "text": " the importance of the gotra or family was stressed."}, {"start": 265.48, "end": 268.48, "text": " Sagotra marriage is not allowed"}, {"start": 268.48, "end": 271.48, "text": " because the progeny will be weak."}, {"start": 271.48, "end": 273.48, "text": " Sagotra marriage."}, {"start": 273.48, "end": 275.48, "text": " The children they conceive will be weak."}, {"start": 275.48, "end": 278.48, "text": " So therefore, different gotra, belonging to different gotra,"}, {"start": 278.48, "end": 282.48, "text": " is important for consideration of marriage."}, {"start": 282.48, "end": 285.48, "text": " And Prabhupada gives another example."}, {"start": 285.48, "end": 287.48, "text": " Arjuna also married Subhadra,"}, {"start": 287.48, "end": 289.48, "text": " although she was his matrimony."}, {"start": 289.48, "end": 292.48, "text": " She was his maternal cousin sister."}, {"start": 292.48, "end": 296.48, "text": " Arjuna married Krishna's sister."}, {"start": 296.48, "end": 299.48, "text": " Krishna was the cousin brother of Arjuna"}, {"start": 299.48, "end": 303.48, "text": " because Arjuna's mother Kunti"}, {"start": 303.48, "end": 308.48, "text": " and Krishna's father Vasudeva were sister and brother."}, {"start": 308.48, "end": 312.48, "text": " So therefore, Arjuna and Krishna were cousins."}, {"start": 312.48, "end": 315.48, "text": " But therefore, Arjuna and Krishna,"}, {"start": 315.48, "end": 316.48, "text": " not only Arjuna and Krishna,"}, {"start": 316.48, "end": 318.48, "text": " Arjuna and Subhadra were also cousins."}, {"start": 318.48, "end": 320.48, "text": " How could they marry each other"}, {"start": 320.48, "end": 322.48, "text": " if they were cousins, brother and sister?"}, {"start": 322.48, "end": 325.48, "text": " That is because they belong to a different gotra."}, {"start": 325.48, "end": 329.48, "text": " Now Srila Prabhupada in the purport explains"}, {"start": 329.48, "end": 334.48, "text": " the brief history of Janamejaya."}, {"start": 334.48, "end": 337.48, "text": " Janamejaya was the eldest son of Parikshit."}, {"start": 337.48, "end": 342.48, "text": " Parikshit begot four sons headed by Janamejaya."}, {"start": 342.48, "end": 347.48, "text": " So Janamejaya's brief history is given by Srila Prabhupada."}, {"start": 348.48, "end": 350.48, "text": " He says,"}, {"start": 350.48, "end": 352.48, "text": " one of the Rajarshi kings"}, {"start": 352.48, "end": 355.48, "text": " and the famous son of Maharaj Parikshit,"}, {"start": 355.48, "end": 356.48, "text": " Janamejaya,"}, {"start": 356.48, "end": 358.48, "text": " is a Rajarshi,"}, {"start": 358.48, "end": 360.48, "text": " a saintly king,"}, {"start": 360.48, "end": 362.48, "text": " Raja, Rishi."}, {"start": 362.48, "end": 364.48, "text": " Both Raja and Rishi."}, {"start": 364.48, "end": 367.48, "text": " That means he is a saintly king."}, {"start": 367.48, "end": 370.48, "text": " His mother's name was Iravati."}, {"start": 370.48, "end": 373.48, "text": " Janamejaya's mother's name was Iravati."}, {"start": 373.48, "end": 375.48, "text": " Or according to some,"}, {"start": 375.48, "end": 377.48, "text": " Madravati."}, {"start": 378.48, "end": 383.48, "text": " Maharaj Janamejaya begot two sons of the names"}, {"start": 383.48, "end": 387.48, "text": " Gnatanika and Shankukarna."}, {"start": 387.48, "end": 393.48, "text": " He celebrated several sacrifices in the Kurukshetra pilgrimage site."}, {"start": 393.48, "end": 395.48, "text": " This Janamejaya,"}, {"start": 395.48, "end": 399.48, "text": " later on it will be described that Maharaj Parikshit"}, {"start": 399.48, "end": 403.48, "text": " handed over charge of ruling the world"}, {"start": 403.48, "end": 406.48, "text": " to his eldest son Janamejaya."}, {"start": 406.48, "end": 408.48, "text": " When Parikshit retired"}, {"start": 408.48, "end": 410.48, "text": " from his royal duties,"}, {"start": 410.48, "end": 412.48, "text": " when he was cursed"}, {"start": 412.48, "end": 416.48, "text": " to die within seven days by a snake bite."}, {"start": 416.48, "end": 419.48, "text": " Those incidents will be described in the later chapters."}, {"start": 419.48, "end": 424.48, "text": " So therefore it is described when Janamejaya took charge of ruling"}, {"start": 424.48, "end": 427.48, "text": " the world from his father Parikshit."}, {"start": 427.48, "end": 433.48, "text": " He also got married and he begot two sons of the names Gnatanika and Shankukarna."}, {"start": 433.48, "end": 435.48, "text": " These emperors or kings"}, {"start": 435.48, "end": 437.48, "text": " were very responsible"}, {"start": 437.48, "end": 440.48, "text": " in leaving behind a"}, {"start": 440.48, "end": 443.48, "text": " well trained,"}, {"start": 443.48, "end": 446.48, "text": " qualified successor."}, {"start": 446.48, "end": 449.48, "text": " For the welfare of the world,"}, {"start": 449.48, "end": 453.48, "text": " for ruling the world properly,"}, {"start": 453.48, "end": 455.48, "text": " there is a need for"}, {"start": 455.48, "end": 457.48, "text": " a good Kshatriya,"}, {"start": 457.48, "end": 459.48, "text": " a qualified Kshatriya,"}, {"start": 459.48, "end": 461.48, "text": " a proper Kshatriya to rule the world"}, {"start": 461.48, "end": 463.48, "text": " for the welfare of the citizens."}, {"start": 463.48, "end": 465.48, "text": " So these,"}, {"start": 465.48, "end": 466.48, "text": " these emperors,"}, {"start": 466.48, "end": 469.48, "text": " they themselves were very good rulers"}, {"start": 469.48, "end": 472.48, "text": " and they also begot"}, {"start": 472.48, "end": 474.48, "text": " good children,"}, {"start": 474.48, "end": 477.48, "text": " satsantana,"}, {"start": 477.48, "end": 480.48, "text": " by the proper"}, {"start": 480.48, "end": 482.48, "text": " process,"}, {"start": 482.48, "end": 483.48, "text": " by the proper methods,"}, {"start": 483.48, "end": 486.48, "text": " by following the proper instructions"}, {"start": 486.48, "end": 492.48, "text": " of the bona fide spiritual authorities."}, {"start": 492.48, "end": 494.48, "text": " Then it is described here,"}, {"start": 494.48, "end": 497.48, "text": " Janamejaya celebrated several sacrifices"}, {"start": 497.48, "end": 500.48, "text": " in the Kurukshetra pilgrimage site."}, {"start": 500.48, "end": 503.48, "text": " Kurukshetra is famous for"}, {"start": 503.48, "end": 505.48, "text": " being a holy place."}, {"start": 505.48, "end": 508.48, "text": " Dharmakshetre Kurukshetre."}, {"start": 508.48, "end": 510.48, "text": " The beginning of Bhagavad Gita,"}, {"start": 510.48, "end": 511.48, "text": " it is described,"}, {"start": 511.48, "end": 513.48, "text": " Kurukshetra is Dharmakshetra,"}, {"start": 513.48, "end": 515.48, "text": " holy place."}, {"start": 515.48, "end": 518.48, "text": " A place where religious rituals are performed."}, {"start": 518.48, "end": 520.48, "text": " It is a very sacred place."}, {"start": 520.48, "end": 522.48, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 522.48, "end": 525.48, "text": " this Janamejaya,"}, {"start": 525.48, "end": 528.48, "text": " he performed several sacrifices in Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 528.48, "end": 530.48, "text": " Why would they perform sacrifices?"}, {"start": 530.48, "end": 534.48, "text": " For the welfare of the citizens."}, {"start": 534.48, "end": 537.48, "text": " They are really responsible kings."}, {"start": 537.48, "end": 540.48, "text": " And it is also described here,"}, {"start": 540.48, "end": 542.48, "text": " Janamejaya had three younger brothers"}, {"start": 542.48, "end": 543.48, "text": " named Shrutasena,"}, {"start": 543.48, "end": 544.48, "text": " Ugrasena,"}, {"start": 544.48, "end": 546.48, "text": " and Bhimasena II."}, {"start": 546.48, "end": 548.48, "text": " So he had three younger brothers also."}, {"start": 548.48, "end": 550.48, "text": " He invaded"}, {"start": 550.48, "end": 553.48, "text": " Takshashila Rajanta"}, {"start": 553.48, "end": 555.48, "text": " and he decided to avenge"}, {"start": 555.48, "end": 557.48, "text": " the unlawful curse upon his great father,"}, {"start": 557.48, "end": 559.48, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit."}, {"start": 559.48, "end": 561.48, "text": " Later on it will be described that is,"}, {"start": 561.48, "end": 565.48, "text": " Pariksit was cursed to die by snake bite."}, {"start": 565.48, "end": 566.48, "text": " So this Janamejaya,"}, {"start": 566.48, "end": 568.48, "text": " when he learnt about it,"}, {"start": 568.48, "end": 574.48, "text": " he wanted to take revenge against"}, {"start": 574.48, "end": 579.48, "text": " the snake which bit his father."}, {"start": 579.48, "end": 582.48, "text": " According to the curse."}, {"start": 582.48, "end": 585.48, "text": " So what did he do to take revenge?"}, {"start": 585.48, "end": 586.48, "text": " This is Janamejaya."}, {"start": 586.48, "end": 588.48, "text": " He performed a great sacrifice"}, {"start": 588.48, "end": 590.48, "text": " called Sarpayagna."}, {"start": 590.48, "end": 594.48, "text": " To kill the race of serpents."}, {"start": 594.48, "end": 597.48, "text": " He wanted to kill all the snakes."}, {"start": 597.48, "end": 600.48, "text": " Because one serpent bit his father."}, {"start": 600.48, "end": 603.48, "text": " Of course,"}, {"start": 603.48, "end": 607.48, "text": " his real anger was against Takshaka,"}, {"start": 607.48, "end": 608.48, "text": " one of the serpents."}, {"start": 608.48, "end": 611.48, "text": " One of the serpents"}, {"start": 611.48, "end": 613.48, "text": " who bit his father."}, {"start": 613.48, "end": 615.48, "text": " Because his father was cursed"}, {"start": 615.48, "end": 617.48, "text": " to die by snake bite."}, {"start": 617.48, "end": 619.48, "text": " Particularly Takshaka's bite."}, {"start": 619.48, "end": 623.48, "text": " So this Janamejaya arranged a"}, {"start": 623.48, "end": 627.48, "text": " Sarpayagna to be performed by qualified Brahmanas."}, {"start": 627.48, "end": 629.48, "text": " And his aim was"}, {"start": 629.48, "end": 632.48, "text": " to kill the race of serpents,"}, {"start": 632.48, "end": 634.48, "text": " including Takshaka."}, {"start": 634.48, "end": 637.48, "text": " Now on request from many influential"}, {"start": 637.48, "end": 639.48, "text": " demigods and sages,"}, {"start": 639.48, "end": 641.48, "text": " he had to change his decision"}, {"start": 641.48, "end": 645.48, "text": " to kill the race of serpents."}, {"start": 645.48, "end": 648.48, "text": " That means,"}, {"start": 648.48, "end": 651.48, "text": " when he undertook this sacrifice,"}, {"start": 651.48, "end": 653.48, "text": " he was told by,"}, {"start": 653.48, "end": 656.48, "text": " advised by many influential devatas"}, {"start": 656.48, "end": 658.48, "text": " and sages and saintly persons,"}, {"start": 658.48, "end": 660.48, "text": " don't do this."}, {"start": 660.48, "end": 663.48, "text": " Don't simply kill all the serpents."}, {"start": 663.48, "end": 665.48, "text": " This is unfair."}, {"start": 665.48, "end": 666.48, "text": " This is not proper."}, {"start": 667.48, "end": 672.48, "text": " And then he actually agreed"}, {"start": 672.48, "end": 674.48, "text": " to stop the sacrifice"}, {"start": 674.48, "end": 677.48, "text": " when he was instructed or advised"}, {"start": 677.48, "end": 680.48, "text": " by many saintly persons and even devatas"}, {"start": 680.48, "end": 682.48, "text": " not to do this kind of sacrifice"}, {"start": 682.48, "end": 685.48, "text": " to kill all the serpents."}, {"start": 685.48, "end": 688.48, "text": " But in spite of stopping the sacrifice,"}, {"start": 688.48, "end": 690.48, "text": " what did Janamejaya do?"}, {"start": 690.48, "end": 692.48, "text": " He satisfied everyone concerned"}, {"start": 692.48, "end": 695.48, "text": " in the sacrifice by rewarding them properly."}, {"start": 695.48, "end": 697.48, "text": " He gave the proper Dakshina,"}, {"start": 697.48, "end": 700.48, "text": " even though the sacrifice was stopped."}, {"start": 700.48, "end": 702.48, "text": " It was not conducted."}, {"start": 702.48, "end": 705.48, "text": " But he did give the Dakshina"}, {"start": 705.48, "end": 707.48, "text": " to the sages,"}, {"start": 707.48, "end": 710.48, "text": " to the brahmanas who were"}, {"start": 710.48, "end": 713.48, "text": " appointed for performing the sacrifice."}, {"start": 713.48, "end": 715.48, "text": " In this ceremony,"}, {"start": 715.48, "end": 717.48, "text": " Maharaj, sorry,"}, {"start": 717.48, "end": 719.48, "text": " Mahamuni Vyasadeva was also present"}, {"start": 719.48, "end": 721.48, "text": " in the sarpayagna,"}, {"start": 721.48, "end": 723.48, "text": " preparation for sarpayagna."}, {"start": 723.48, "end": 725.48, "text": " And he personally narrated"}, {"start": 725.48, "end": 727.48, "text": " the history of the battle of Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 727.48, "end": 730.48, "text": " before King Janamejaya."}, {"start": 730.48, "end": 732.48, "text": " So Vyasadeva,"}, {"start": 732.48, "end": 736.48, "text": " he is an incarnation of the Supreme Lord"}, {"start": 736.48, "end": 740.48, "text": " for the sake of preparing the scriptures,"}, {"start": 740.48, "end": 743.48, "text": " especially the scriptures for the"}, {"start": 743.48, "end": 745.48, "text": " people of Kali Yuga"}, {"start": 745.48, "end": 747.48, "text": " and the common people."}, {"start": 747.48, "end": 750.48, "text": " So Mahamuni Vyasadeva was present"}, {"start": 750.48, "end": 752.48, "text": " in that sacrifice and"}, {"start": 752.48, "end": 755.48, "text": " he personally narrated the history of"}, {"start": 755.48, "end": 757.48, "text": " the battle of Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 757.48, "end": 759.48, "text": " to Janamejaya."}, {"start": 759.48, "end": 760.48, "text": " How?"}, {"start": 760.48, "end": 763.48, "text": " Janamejaya's great grandfather,"}, {"start": 763.48, "end": 766.48, "text": " Pariksit's grandfather is Arjuna."}, {"start": 766.48, "end": 769.48, "text": " So Janamejaya's great grandfather is Arjuna."}, {"start": 769.48, "end": 772.48, "text": " How Arjuna fought in the battle of Kurukshetra,"}, {"start": 772.48, "end": 775.48, "text": " how Arjuna was instructed by Krishna,"}, {"start": 775.48, "end": 778.48, "text": " how Arjuna conducted himself very bravely,"}, {"start": 778.48, "end": 781.48, "text": " etc., etc."}, {"start": 781.48, "end": 782.48, "text": " Later on,"}, {"start": 782.48, "end": 785.48, "text": " by the order of Vyasadeva,"}, {"start": 785.48, "end": 786.48, "text": " Vyasadeva's disciple,"}, {"start": 786.48, "end": 787.48, "text": " Narayana,"}, {"start": 787.48, "end": 789.48, "text": " narrated before King Janamejaya"}, {"start": 789.48, "end": 793.48, "text": " the subject matter of Mahabharata."}, {"start": 793.48, "end": 799.48, "text": " Now the Bhagavad Gita is a small portion of Mahabharata."}, {"start": 799.48, "end": 802.48, "text": " The Mahabharata is the history of greater India."}, {"start": 802.48, "end": 805.48, "text": " It is a very, very big scripture."}, {"start": 805.48, "end": 808.48, "text": " While Bhagavad Gita has 700 verses,"}, {"start": 808.48, "end": 812.48, "text": " Mahabharata has 100,000 verses"}, {"start": 812.48, "end": 815.48, "text": " or one lakh verses."}, {"start": 815.48, "end": 820.48, "text": " Mahabharata has lakh shlokas."}, {"start": 820.48, "end": 825.48, "text": " Bhagavatam has only 18,000 shlokas."}, {"start": 825.48, "end": 828.48, "text": " Mahabharata has one lakh shlokas."}, {"start": 828.48, "end": 831.48, "text": " So that Mahabharata"}, {"start": 831.48, "end": 834.48, "text": " was narrated to Janamejaya"}, {"start": 834.48, "end": 838.48, "text": " by Vaishampayana,"}, {"start": 838.48, "end": 839.48, "text": " Rishi,"}, {"start": 839.48, "end": 843.48, "text": " who was a disciple of Vyasadeva."}, {"start": 843.48, "end": 844.48, "text": " On the instruction of Vyasadeva,"}, {"start": 844.48, "end": 846.48, "text": " he did so."}, {"start": 846.48, "end": 849.48, "text": " So this Janamejaya was affected very much"}, {"start": 849.48, "end": 853.48, "text": " by the father's untimely death."}, {"start": 853.48, "end": 855.48, "text": " And he expressed his desire to"}, {"start": 855.48, "end": 856.48, "text": " Vedavyasa,"}, {"start": 856.48, "end": 858.48, "text": " I want to see my father again."}, {"start": 858.48, "end": 862.48, "text": " And Vyasadeva fulfilled his desire."}, {"start": 862.48, "end": 866.48, "text": " So when his father was presented by Vyasadeva,"}, {"start": 866.48, "end": 868.48, "text": " that is Pariksit,"}, {"start": 868.48, "end": 873.48, "text": " then both Pariksit and Vyasadeva were worshipped."}, {"start": 873.48, "end": 877.48, "text": " They were worshipped by Janamejaya."}, {"start": 877.48, "end": 881.48, "text": " And being fully satisfied"}, {"start": 881.48, "end": 886.48, "text": " when he was able to see his father"}, {"start": 886.48, "end": 889.48, "text": " due to the mercy of Vyasadeva,"}, {"start": 889.48, "end": 894.48, "text": " then he very liberally gave Dakshina"}, {"start": 894.48, "end": 897.48, "text": " to all the brahmanas present at the sacrifice"}, {"start": 897.48, "end": 901.48, "text": " and satisfied them completely."}, {"start": 901.48, "end": 903.48, "text": " This is very important."}, {"start": 903.48, "end": 906.48, "text": " A king's duty to give in charity"}, {"start": 906.48, "end": 908.48, "text": " to especially the brahmanas"}, {"start": 908.48, "end": 909.48, "text": " because brahmanas,"}, {"start": 909.48, "end": 913.48, "text": " they don't charge any fees."}, {"start": 913.48, "end": 920.48, "text": " They don't collect any amount"}, {"start": 920.48, "end": 924.48, "text": " as their fees for giving advice"}, {"start": 924.48, "end": 928.48, "text": " or instructions or directing the people."}, {"start": 928.48, "end": 931.48, "text": " But that doesn't mean that people simply take"}, {"start": 931.48, "end": 934.48, "text": " advice or instructions or directions"}, {"start": 934.48, "end": 935.48, "text": " without giving anything."}, {"start": 935.48, "end": 940.48, "text": " They give something according to their means."}, {"start": 940.48, "end": 945.48, "text": " Dakshina, that's called dana or dakshina."}, {"start": 945.48, "end": 947.48, "text": " And the brahmanas are satisfied"}, {"start": 947.48, "end": 950.48, "text": " with very minimum."}, {"start": 950.48, "end": 951.48, "text": " But kings,"}, {"start": 951.48, "end": 955.48, "text": " they reward brahmanas very liberally"}, {"start": 955.48, "end": 957.48, "text": " because kings are very rich."}, {"start": 957.48, "end": 959.48, "text": " So that the brahmanas"}, {"start": 959.48, "end": 961.48, "text": " needn't have any anxiety"}, {"start": 961.48, "end": 963.48, "text": " about their maintenance."}, {"start": 963.48, "end": 965.48, "text": " That's the principle."}, {"start": 965.48, "end": 966.48, "text": " I'll stop here."}, {"start": 966.48, "end": 967.48, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 967.48, "end": 968.48, "text": " Hare Krishna."}]}